File: Telkom will offer business loans and digital wallet services. JOHANNESBURG - Telkom is entering the financial services market. It's targetting over 11 million South Africans who do not have bank accounts. Its fixed-line service will remain the core of the business. READ: Telkom profits down 66% That business currently contributes over 20 percent of the group's revenue. In 2013, it contributed over 50 percent. The partly state-owned enterprise will offer business loans and digital wallet services. A few weeks ago, Telkom transformed its 70-year-old Yellow Pages business into an online marketplace targeting SMEs which it named Yep.